I read all 12 reviews before I bought this DVD because I figured at least one of them would name the four movies on them. No such luck. The first movie is Gone to Texas starring Sam Elliot who plays Sam Houston during the period after the Alamo and before Texas became a state. I will fight no more forever with Sam Elliot about the Nez Pierce tribe of indians who were the last indians forced onto a reservation and how they were forced onto the reservation. Superdome with cameo appearances from Tom Selleck about a football team that was expected to win the superbowl and how gamblers went about trying to cause the team to lose so they could win their bet. This is the only movie that had Tom Sellect in it and he does not wear a hat liked pictured on the DVD case. Blue river with Sam Elliot about two brothers who had been estranged for 15 years and how they because estranged. I already had the first 2 and did not like the last 2. If someone had listed the movies I would not have bought this DVD.
